<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.7 on the
open-ended Richter scale hit Bingol province in eastern Turkey
today, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted officials of Istanbul's Kandilli Seimological
Center as saying that the quake occurred in Bingol at 14:23
GMT and so far no immediate reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
The officials said that the tremor also affected the
provinces of Erzurum and Tunceli.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was reported to be Karliova
town of Bingol.
</P>
<P>
Earthquakes measuring between 4 and 5 on the Richter scale
are described as powerful enough to cause casualties in a
populated area.
</P>
<P>
Local press reported that 92 percent of Turkish land faces
the risk of earthquake, 95 percent of the population and 96
percent of Turkish industry are located at the earthquake zone.
</P>
</TEXT>
