<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Warns against Relaxation on Farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng cautioned
here today that agriculture must not be neglected following a
record harvest last year.
</P>
<P>
In a group discussion with Henan deputies to the Eighth
National People's Congress in session here, Li said that China's
record grain output of 480 billion kg last year should not be
regarded as an entirely true indication of the level of China's
agricultural production, as the weather last year was favorable
for crops.
</P>
<P>
"After a big harvest, we must not relax with regard to
agriculture and grain production," the premier said. "We must be
sober-minded."
</P>
<P>
He said that Henan, a major wheat producer with a population of
90 million, must not neglect the production of wheat, though it
reported a good harvest last year.
</P>
<P>
"We must keep in mind that there are bumper years and lean
years in our country's agricultural production," Li said, quoting
a Chinese maxim "get prepared for danger in times of peace."
</P>
<P>
"We have established a grain reserve system in recent
years," he said. "Though at some costs, we have had to do so to
ensure an ample grain supply in case natural disasters strike."
</P>
<P>
China has established a household-based farming system since it
launched the economic reform and opening-up drive in the late
1970s and today it is still a good policy able to arouse the
enthusiasm of farmers, the premier said,
</P>
<P>
"The policy should be further improved and developed," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that efforts should be made to develop the social
service sector and rural enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In many places, rural enterprises processing farm produce have
helped raise the income of farmers, he said.
</P>
<P>
"In the long-term, rural enterprises have a good prospect for
development," Li said.
</P>
<P>
On harnessing the Yellow River, China's second longest running
through Henan, Li said that the river was a cradle of the Chinese
nation but its floods pose serious trouble and danger.
</P>
<P>
Safety along the river has been the result of construction of a
number of water conservancy facilities, now eight at the upper
reach, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called for accelerating the construction of the Xiaolangdi
Project, which is expected to greatly increase safety along the
middle and lower reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
"The problem of the Yellow River is not yet resolved and needs
comprehensive harnessing," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said China's economic development is not balanced and an
earnest effort must be made to reduce poverty, pledging that
existing funds and preferential policies for poverty relief will
be maintained in a period of time to come.
</P>
<P>
He added that as the national economy grows and the country
becomes financially more powerful, the government will increase
spending on poverty relief.
</P>
<P>
He called on the deputies to work hard and practice thrift in
order to get rid of backwardness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
