<HEADLINE> Poland Upsets Malaysia in World Cup Hockey Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Poland clinched a surprise
win over host Malaysia while South Korea, New Zealand and Belgium
all enjoyed easy victory at the opening round of men's World Cup
hockey qualifiers here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Host Malaysia, came from a 16-year absence from the World Cup
series, was upset 5-4 by Poland in the only Group A match of the
day.
</P>
<P>
Asian champions South Korea clinched a 4-2 victory over Belarus
in the Group B.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans, who finished eighth in the last World Cup in
Sydney in 1994, used their speed and agility to take a 3-1 lead in
the first-half despite the humid weather.
</P>
<P>
World Cup regulars Argentina, seventh in Sydney, was suffered a
big set back by New Zealand 3-1 in the same group.
</P>
<P>
Belgium turned out a 2-1 winner over Ireland also Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The top six teams in this 12-team tournament will qualify for
the World Cup finals in the Netherlands in May next year.
</P>
<P>
The six will join defending champions Pakistan, the
Netherlands, Australia, Germany, India and England. Endtiem

