<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Leader Calls for Assistance to Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A ranking Chinese official today
calls on governments at all levels to try their best to guarantee
the basic needs of the laid-off workers from the state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Both long-term measures that address the root cause of
unemployment and some emergency ones are required to help those in
want, said Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of Communist Party of China Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
With China's ongoing efforts to reshuffle its failing
state-owned sector, a growing number of people have lost their
jobs and found it increasingly difficult to make both ends meet.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is also chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), called
for establishing special bodies to deal with the problem in an
all-round way, while attending a panel discussion of the Tianjin
deputies to the ongoing session of the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The head of China's top advisory body suggested specific
measures to be taken for tackling the problem. "We should rather
cut back the number of new projects and slow down the growth
speed, to ensure that people will have enough to eat."
</P>
<P>
Some public welfare projects should be launched to create more
jobs opportunities, and people should be encouraged to carry on
the traditional virtue of helping the needy and establish charity
funds, he suggested.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Li noted, some funds should be raised among those
people on jobs, individual income taxes should be adjusted and
other methods used to help the laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
More work should be done, education enhanced and new concepts
on jobs selection should be fostered, Li said. "If there is a job
but you rejects it, and then the government is not to blame."
</P>
<P>
A growing number of the unemployed is an unavoidable phenomenon
during the course of establishing a socialist market economy,
since the market competition necessitates the elimination of those
poorly managed, he explains.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted, since the problem concerns the livelihood of
some people, which will have a direct bearing on social stability,
and reform and opening-up, it must be handled properly.
</P>
<P>
"The basic purpose of the Communist Party and the People's
government is to serve the people whole-heartedly, and the problem
must be addressed," Li affirmed.
</P>
<P>
During the discussion, Li Ruihuan also expressed his approval
of Premier Li Peng's government work report to the current NPC
session, and shared views with NPC deputies from Tianjin on topics
ranging from promotion of science and technology, acceleration of
the reform pace of state-owned enterprises, to the role of Tianjin
municipalities (one of China's three existing municipalities) to
be played in national economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
