<HEADLINE> Uganda Refutes South Africa's Press Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government has
refuted press reports by South Africa's Sunday Times that ''South
Africa arms to Uganda dent Sudan peace''.
</P>
<P>
A statement by Ugandan Minister of State for Regional
Cooperation Rebecca Kadaga clarified here today that not a single
item or equipment of arms supplied to Uganda has ever ended up
with the Sudanese People's Liberation Army (SPLA) rebels, the
government of Rwanda, or any other organisation outside Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has always strictly adhered to the stipulations of the
end user certificates, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
The statement further said that the false allegations in the
press are intended to discredit Uganda's international image and
are reminiscent of the repeated baseless propaganda by the Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's major newspapers such as The New Vision and The
Monitor repeated the reports of South Africa on March 3,
1997. enditem

