<HEADLINE> Menuhin Honored by Germany with Highest Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Master violinist Yehudi Menuhin
received here today Germany's highest civilian honor, the grand
cross of the Order of the Federal Republic of Germany.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony at the state guesthouse in the suburbs of Bonn,
German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel said the award was to honour
Menuhin as one of the greatest musicians and outstanding
personalities of the century.
</P>
<P>
Menuhin, who holds joint U.S., Swiss and British nationality,
was born in the United States on April 22, 1916. Apart from his
musical mastership, he is also honored for his contributions to
music education worldwide. 
</P>
