<HEADLINE> Algeria to Hold General Elections on June 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Algeria will hold general
elections on June 5 to put into place a new two-chamber
parliament, the Algerian television quoted a government communique
as saying today.
</P>
<P>
The date was fixed during a meeting today between the leaders
of nine major opposition parties of the country and President
Liamine Zeroual, held within the framework of a new series of
consultations on the establishment of a Supervision Commission for
the Legislative Elections (CNISEL).
</P>
<P>
Among the parties which took part in today's consultation were
the Rassemblement pour la Culture and la Democratie, le Front de
Liberation Nationale and le Mouvement de la Societe Islamique.
</P>
<P>
President Zeroual proposed the election date at May 29 or June
5 at an earlier meeting with the oppositions.
</P>
<P>
The president said that the polling in the general elections
will be carried out in total security and under observation of
officials from United Nations, the Arab League and the
Organization of African Unity.
</P>
<P>
Algerian political parties agreed to hold the general elections
during a meeting of national harmony held last October. 
</P>
