of dear parts of Lebanon, which are still occupied despite the
U.N. resolution 425."
</P>
<P>
He said Israel should implement all U.N. Security Council
resolutions related to its aggression against his country,
especially resolution 425, which calls for an immediate and
unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel's 1978 invasion of Lebanon resulted in the
establishment of what later became the so-called "security zone"
to curb cross-border guerrillas activities against northern
Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese speaker also stressed that the Middle East peace
process was threatened by "Israeli attempts to judaize Jerusalem
and its repeated aggression against Lebanon."
</P>
<P>
He was referring to the recent Israeli decision to expand the
Jewish settlement in Har Homa of East Jerusalem by building 6,500
new houses for the Jews.
</P>
