<HEADLINE> AL Chief Calls on Asia to Support Arab Cause </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General Esmat
Abdel-Meguid today called upon Asian countries to increase their
diplomatic support for the Arab and the Palestinian cause,
according to the Egyptian Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting today with ambassadors from eight Asian
countries accredited to Egypt, Meguid said outside help is
especially important when Israel tries to intensify its
settlement schemes in Eastern Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Israeli government continues its settlement
practices, thus violating the Madrid peace conference resolutions
and agreements concluded with the Palestinians, especially those
connected with Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"Israel, through these practices, aims to change Jerusalem's
demographic character in order to strike a new reality in this
holy city prior to the final phase negotiations," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the Arab leader said Israel should realize that the
Arab countries are not joining the peace negotiations because
they are weak.
</P>
<P>
"Instead, our belief in peace as the strategic option is out
of strength and confidence in the importance of peace to all
parties," he said, adding Israel cannot impose long-lasting peace
by force.
</P>
<P>
He said that Asian countries, especially China, Japan and
India, enjoy strong ties with the Arab states and consistently
support the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
The ambassadors, in their turn, reiterated their countries'
support for all U.N. Security Council resolutions on the
Palestinian issue, especially 242 and 338. They stressed the
importance of enhancing Arab-Asian relations.
</P>
<P>
Their countries do not recognize Israel's annexation of
Jerusalem in the 1967 Mideast War, said the ambassadors from
China, India, Japan, Bangladesh, Indonesia, the Philippines, Sri
Lanka and Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
