possible," he said. adding that "There is no question of buying
Russia off or compensating them for (NATO) enlargement."
</P>
<P>
"I believe that Russia will ultimately come to the conclusion
that a privileged relationship with an enlarged NATO is far
preferable to any other alternative," he added.
</P>
<P>
Solana also held separate talks with British Prime Minister
John Major and Defense Secretary Michael Portillo earlier today to
exchange views on NATO expansion and other issues of common
concern. 
</P>
