<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister of Cameroun Peter
Musonge today urged African supreme auditing institutions to
secure the credibility, transparency and efficiency in the
management of public finance.
</P>
<P>
Musonge made the remarks while presiding over the 7th general
assembly meeting of the Organization of African Higher
Institution of Public Finance Control (AFROSAI) at the Conference
Center in Yaounde this morning.
