<HEADLINE> IBM Dives Into China's High-tech Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- IBM has decided to build a
second joint venture in China to secure a strong foothold in the
country's high-tech manufacturing industry.
</P>
<P>
IBM, China Great Wall Computer Shenzhen Company and Shenzhen
Koifa Technology Co. Ltd. will together invest 42.5 million
U.S. dollars to set up a manufacturing company in Shenzhen, the
special economic zone bordering Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Hailiang Storage Products Co. (Hailiang) will
produce a key component of the hard disk drive, called
magnetoresistive head gimbal assemblies (HGA), for IBM's hard disk
 drive assembly plants worldwide.
</P>
<P>
When fully operational, Hailiang is expected to have an annual
production capacity of 30 million HGAs.
</P>
<P>
It is the second cooperative project between the three
partners, which in 1995 established the Shenzhen GKI Electronics
Co. Ltd. to develop and produce circuit cards.  
</P>
</TEXT>
