<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Solution to New Problems (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today calls for the whole Party and the whole nation to seek
solutions to new problems at a time when China is pushing ahead
with its reform, opening-up and modernization programs.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also the General Secretary of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and Chairman of
the Central Military Commission, made the remark when he joined
deputies to the National People's Congress (NPC) from Hunan and
Guangdong in discussing Premier Li Peng's government work report.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said, "Problems encountered in practice can only be
further understood in practice, and correct solutions to problems
can only be sought in practice."
</P>
<P>
At the discussion with Hunan deputies, Jiang said that Hunan is
an agricultural province, and great efforts should continue to
boost its agriculture and rural economy.
</P>
<P>
He listed aspects that merit special efforts, including
improvement of basic farming facilities, diversification of rural
operations, development of rural enterprises, industrialization of
production processes, and use of science and technology in
boosting agricultural production, "so that Hunan will develop its
agriculture and rural economy to a higher level," he said.
</P>
<P>
"This is also a realistic way for agricultural provinces to
develop themselves into economic powerhouses," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that water conservancy facilities are among
the most important for farming.
</P>
<P>
Hunan has been hit by severe floods in recent years, he
pointed out, which resulted from both natural causes and
inadequate facilities.
</P>
<P>
"The first thing to do is to harness the Dongting Lake, which
is also an important part of the effort to harness the Yangtze
River," he said.
</P>
<P>
The president said reform, restructuring and renovation of the
province's industry should continue, and efforts should be made to
rejuvenate state-owned enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
