<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Solution to New Problems (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The key to overcoming difficulties faced by state-owned
enterprises lies in boosting people's confidence and in deepening
reform, Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He called on the provincial government to focus on improvement
of pillar industries and enterprise groups that enjoy remarkable
advantages and development potential and whose products conform
with the state industrial policy and are needed on the market so
that they can promote the development of the entire provincial
economy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called on the province to open wider to the outside
world, improve the quality of opening up, and actively develop
economic and technological cooperation with overseas partners.
</P>
<P>
He also called on Hunan to develop economic cooperation with
western and eastern China, for common development and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
He urged the provincial authorities to help people in
flood-stricken areas to rebuild their homes and resume work,
guarantee the basic livelihood of employees of poorly run
enterprises, and help the 3.5 million rural poor to have enough to
eat and wear.
</P>
<P>
In the discussion with deputies from Guangdong, Jiang said
Guangdong has made new progresses in reform and development,
as reflected by its smooth economic performance and the
effectiveness of macroeconomic control measures there.
</P>
<P>
He said that the late Deng Xiaoping had shown great concern for
reform and development in Guangdong and in its three special
economic zones (SEZ) of Shenzhen, Zhuhai and Shantou, and that his
inspection of south China in 1992 fueled reform and development
there.
</P>
<P>
"In accordance with Comrade Deng Xiaoping's instructions,
Guangdong should try to achieve basic modernization by the year
2010," he said, noting that ethical and cultural progress in the
province should keep pace with its economic development.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the provincial authorities would "do
a better job of reform and development in Guangdong and in its
three SEZs" so that the province will continue to lead the country
in this regard and meet what Deng Xiaoping expected of it and the
Party Central Committee expects of it.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that acceleration of economic development in the
eastern part of the country, including Guangdong, will promote
development in the central and western parts and the country.
</P>
<P>
"It is a significant decision made by Deng Xiaoping and the
Party Central Committee that the eastern region should get
developed first to bring along and advance the eventual
development of the whole country to achieve common prosperity," he
said.
</P>
