<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1500 GMT, March 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA -- Dhaka and Manila agreed on Wednesday to revive the
Joint Economic Commission in a bid to enhance and expand
bilateral cooperation in trade, economic, technical fields.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed at a joint press conference by Bangladeshi
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina and visiting President Fidel Ramos
of the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and Israeli Prime
Minister Binyamin Netanyahu held talks here Wednesday on the peace
process, particularly on a new housing project in East Jerusalem
which threatened to block the Middle East peace march.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu came exactly a week after Israel decided to set up
6,500 Jewish homes in Har Homa, a tree-covered hill in East
Jerusalem, taken by Israel in the 1967 Middle East War.
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl met here Wednesday with
visiting U.S. Defence Secretary William Cohen, praising the
relations between Germany and the United States as "outstanding."
</P>
<P>
Cohen is currently on his first trip abroad after becoming
U.S. defence chief.
</P>
<P>
BONN -- Thousands of anti-nuclear protesters were dispersed by
police water cannons in northern Germany Wednesday morning as they
were trying to block the transport of nuclear waste to a nearby
storage depot.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean President Kim Young-sam Wednesday
replaced 10 out of 28 cabinet ministers in a wide-ranging
government shake-up following Tuesday's appointment of Koh Kun as
the new prime minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
