located in Nanhai, Guangdong, and said he admires Guangdong's
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
During his China tour, Bouterse has visited Beijing, Shanghai
and Guilin. He siad he was deeply impressed with China's rapid
economic development, and that there are broad prospects for
Surinam-Chinese cooperation and that he hopes that both sides can
increase exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Bouterse and his party will leave for Hong Kong tomorrow.
