<HEADLINE> China Basketball All-Stars Voting Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The vote to elect the 20 All-Stars
players will begin on Thursday in the Chinese men's first division
basketball league, the organizers said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hu Weidong of Jiangsu Nangang, leading scorer in the 22-round
regular season with 30.9 points per game, is expected to lead the
South All-Stars team which concluding players form Jiangsu
Nangang, August First Rockets, Guangdong Tigers, Shanghai
Oriental, Zhejiang Squirrels, and Sichuan Pandas.
</P>
<P>
Gong Xiaobin, runner-up in scoring to Hu Weidong with 29.4 per
game, will take the spotlight in the North All-Stars team, which
including hoopsters from Gong Xiaobin's Shandong Fleming Bulls,
Liaoning hunters, Beijing Ducks, Shenyang Lions, Lianhang Eagles,
and Jinan Pegasus.
</P>
<P>
The country's basketball fans will vote 10 players for each
teams and the starting line-ups will be announced on March 28.
</P>
<P>
The All-Stars game is scheduled in Shanghai in April 5, five
days after the finals of the four-month long league in March 30.
</P>
<P>
It will be the third All-Stars game in China but the first time
that the two stars squads are formed geographically. 
</P>
</TEXT>
