<HEADLINE> Inland Areas to Develop with Self-Reliant Efforts: Qiao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China's top lawmaker Qiao Shi said
here today that with increasing support from the central
government, central and western provinces and regions should work
still harder and depend themselves for the economic development.
</P>
<P>
Qiao made the call when attending a group meeting of the
Guizhou Delegation of the Fifth Session of the National People's
Congress (NPC) to deliberate the government work report delivered
by Premier Li Peng on March 1.
</P>
<P>
He said that central and western areas are less prosperous
than the coastal provinces and cities due to geological and
historical reasons.
</P>
<P>
But under the leadership of the Party and the government,
people in these areas have made gratifying achievements with their
hard work in all kinds of social and economic causes, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, chairman of the NPC National Committee, pledged the
continued efforts of the central authorities to subsidize and
assist the central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
"With abundant natural resources and the help from the
government, it is quite possible for these areas to develop faster
and better if they go on relying on themselves and work hard by
deepening reforms and opening still wider to the outside world,"
said Qiao, who is also a Standing Committee member of the
Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Economic and technical cooperations and exchanges with coastal
regions must be furthered so as to turn their bountiful resources
into real advantages by absorbing advanced technical and
managerial expertise from the east coastal regions, He stressed.
</P>
<P>
The central government will further encourage the
cooperations and exchanges between the coastal areas with inland
provinces and regions, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao spoke highly of the progress Guizhou province has made
over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
In spite of its large territory, the province has scare arable
lands.
</P>
<P>
Qiao encouraged the province to turn arable mountainsides and
hilly slopes into farmland to produce more grain, to develop
courtyard industries and farm products processing industries
according to local characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The policy of poverty alleviation by means of stimulating
development and production should be adhered and efforts
be further intensified, Qiao said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
