<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi on Economic Development in Ethnic Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China's vast regions inhabited by
ethnic groups are called upon to further promote economic progress
by tapping their potentials and bringing force their advantages,
said Xiao Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC), today.
</P>
<P>
In a group discussion with NPC deputies from Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region, Qiao, who is also a Standing Committee member
of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Committee, said most ethnics are located in remote areas
where economic conditions are poor. However, with the hard efforts
of the national minority people there, great changes have taken
place and much progress has been made.
</P>
<P>
He noted that further efforts should be made to create
conditions for tapping local resources and developing industries
that have local characteristics. In those trades apparent with
strong edges, it is necessary to introduce up-to-date technology
to improve product quality according to international standard.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi expressed his belief that with the support of the
government and joint efforts of all nationalities in the country,
the economy and other undertakings in ethnic regions will score
much greater achievements.
</P>
<P>
Concerning the development of Inner Mongolia over the years,
Qiao said the autonomous region has witnessed fast economic
growth, social stability and ethnic unity. The region has also
made headway in developing agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry
and sideline production and tapping local natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Qiao expressed his belief that Inner Mongolia and other ethnic
areas will make further progress in economic development,
improvement of living conditions and the unity of various ethnic
groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
