<HEADLINE> Vice Premier Calls for Relieving Farmers' Burden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- To increase agricultural
production and farmers' income is the key to relieving the burden
of farmers, said Jiang Chunyun, vice premier of the State Council,
today.
</P>
<P>
In a group discussion with deputies from east China's Jiangxi
Province to the National People's Congress which has been in
session since last Saturday, Jiang said the key to raising
farmers' income is to stabilize sown areas of major crops,
especially grain areas, and work for higher per unit output and
better quality of farm products.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Chunyun, who is also a member of the Communist Party
Central Committee Political Bureau, called for greater efforts to
purchase, process, store and market farm produce.
</P>
<P>
To relieve the financial burden of farmers is an important way
to protect the interests of the farmers and arouse their work
enthusiasm, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called for joint efforts by local governments at various
levels to work for a reduction of farmers' financial burden.
</P>
