<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sculptures of Zhou Enlai and Dong Biwu Completed in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Life-size sculptures of China's
late Premier Zhou Enlai and late Vice-President Dong Biwu, were
completed in the eastern city of Nanjing today to mark the
anniversary of their birthdays.
</P>
<P>
Today is the 99th anniversary of Zhou's birth and the 111th
anniversary of Dong's birth.
</P>
<P>
The sculptures were based on a photo of the two, taken in the
city in 1946, where they were negotiating with the Kuomintang as
representatives of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
The sculptures are made of a special kind of plastic that
reproduces the features of the two great revolutionaries quite
remarkably. They are being put in the Meiyuan Xincun Museum, which
was built on the site where the picture was taken.
</P>
<P>
City government officials and more than 300 teachers and
students attended the unveiling of the sculptures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970305.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Urged to Accelerate Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The key for Sichuan province,
southwest China, is to achieve economic development in a faster
and better way through persevered efforts to center on economic
construction.
</P>
<P>
The remark was made by Hu Jintao, member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee in a panel discussion with Sichuan
deputies in the annual session of the National People's Congress
(NPC), which has been in session since last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hu lauded Sichuan for the great achievements it scored last
year in reform, opening-up and modernization drive, agricultural
production, retooling of state enterprises and infrastructure
construction, in particular.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan is confronted with an excellent opportunity in economic
development, and the sustained, fast and healthy economy across
China has provided it with a good environment, he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
The current NPC session will deliberated on the establishment
of centrally-administered Chongqing municipality, and this, too,
will grant the province with a rare chance for development, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he listed a series of policies formulated by the
Party Central Committee and the State Council to enhance economic
development in the central and western areas, and the construction
of the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
The ranking Party official called on Sichuan officials to
promote local economic development by consolidating the basis of
agriculture, and enhancing reform of the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"The theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
set forth by Deng Xiaoping, and the mature and strong leadership
by the party central committee with Jiang Zemin at its core are a
guarantee to maintain the stability of the party and the state,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Hu urged Sichuan, where late Leader Deng Xiaoping was born, to
carry forward at Deng's behest to build up the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
