<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank's Twenty-four Hour Service Gets Good Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China's Huaxia Bank has set a good
example for the banking sector in Beijing by providing 24-hour
service in China's capital, according to Wang Guangying, the
Vice-Chairman of China's National People's Congress Standing
Committee, who made the comment during a visit to the bank's
office today.
</P>
<P>
Wang said he hopes the bank will improve the service even more,
noting that, "All service industries should develop in a way that
becomes closer to the daily lives of ordinary people and should
adapt to the needs of modern life."
</P>
<P>
Huaxia Bank was set up in 1992 and became a national
share-holding commercial bank in 1995. It has 2.5 billion yuan in
registered capital and its stock is held by 38 enterprises. It has
an office in Beijing and four regional branches in Nanjing, the
capital of Jiangsu Province; Hangzhou, the capital of Zhejiang
Province; Jinan, the capital of Shandong Province; and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1996, it had 15.7 billion yuan in deposits, up
150 percent from the beginning of the year; 9.6 billion yuan in
loans; 23 billion yuan in property, up 88.52 percent from the
beginning of the year; 410 million yuan in profits in 1996, up 108
percent from the previous year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
