<HEADLINE> Algerian Security Forces Kill Three Armed Extremists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Algerian security forces killed
three armed extremists last Saturday in El Bouni, 600 kilometers
east of the capital Algiers, the press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Local inhabitants of El Bouni said the security forces also
seized a number of weapons from the Islamic militants who have
been waging war against the government since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the daily newspaper El Khabar reported today that
four civilians and one Islamic militant were killed Sunday night
in a shoot-out between the militants and members of a self-defense
militia in the village of Khemis El-Khechna, southeast of Algiers.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the civilians were killed in the cross-fire
between the Islamic extremists, riding in two vehicles, and the
militia, organized by the Algerian government to fight terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Another Islamic extremist was wounded in the shoot-out before
he and an unspecified number of other extremists managed to
escape, the report said. 
