<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Exempts Replacement Machinery From Duties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will exempt from import
duties replacement machinery unitizing higher technology in
textile, shoes and food processing industries, the Board of
Investment of Thailand (BOI) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The BOI, chaired by Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh, took
this action in order to enable these industries, which have
recently experienced poor export performance, to obtain the
machinery necessary to improve quality, standards and
attractiveness of their products, according to a BOI press
release.
</P>
<P>
In order to apply for this one-time exemption, the BOI said,
companies in these three sectors must already have been promoted
by the BOI; machinery being purchased must be valued at a minimum
of 1 million baht (40,000 U.S. dollars); and companies must apply
to the BOI for this exemption from import duties on machinery and
may only import machinery duty-free one time within two years of
the date their exemption is granted.
</P>
<P>
This measure will expire on December 31, 1999, the BOI said.
</P>
</TEXT>
