<HEADLINE> Qian Stresses Tibet's Role in Anti-Separatism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister
Qian Qichen said in Beijing today that Tibet has a significant
status in protecting national security and fighting against
separatism.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of all deputies from the Tibet Autonomous Region
to the Eighth National People's Congress, which is in its fifth
session in Beijing, Qian said that the region has scored marked
achievements in economic development, reforms, and opening to the
outside world.
</P>
<P>
"Traditional culture has been well protected in Tibet, which
also enjoys social stability. The attacks and slanders hurled by
some Western media are completely groundless," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that recently some Western newspapers alleged that
culture and traditions in Tibet had been sabotaged, and that
industrial development had disturbed Tibetan people's peaceful
life.
</P>
<P>
"Those who made such allegations should come to Tibet for a
look by themselves," he suggested.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Tibetan culture, including religious belief,
spoken and written language, culture, arts and literature, and
cultural relics and historic sites, is under good protection,
while the autonomous region enjoys economic prosperity and social
stability.
</P>
<P>
"International anti-China forces often used the Tibet issue and
Dalai Lama as their tools," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore Tibet, as an important frontier defence in the
southwestern part of our country, has a significant role in the
struggle of safeguarding the motherland and opposing separatism,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
At present, he noted, China has maintained peace and stability
in its relations with neighboring countries, and trade is active
in quite a number of border areas.
</P>
<P>
"We have also improved relations with India, which is not only
in the interest of both countries, but also conducive to the
reform and opening up in Tibet," he added.
</P>
<P>
He finally expressed his conviction that with powerful backing
of the central authorities, Tibet will make greater progress in
the maintenance of stability and unity, economic development, and
reform and opening-up.  
</P>
</TEXT>
