<HEADLINE> Regional Industrial Output Rises in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- All the Chinese provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions generated a total value of
industrial output of 378.75 billion yuan in last January,
increasing by 11.38 percent from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The top three industrial powerhouses of the country were the
provinces of Jiangsu, Guangdong and Shandong, in terms of the
output value.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu turned out 51.83 billion yuan in industrial output
value in January, up 6.14 percent from that of the same period of
1996.
</P>
<P>
That of Guangdong was 41 billion yuan, representing a
year-on-year increase of 16.85 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of Shandong was 31.99 billion yuan, which is an increment
of 13.79 percent over that of January 1996. 
</P>
