<HEADLINE> Guangxi Achieved Bumper Harvest Despite Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region achieved a record harvest last year despite a
severe flood.
</P>
<P>
The province's grain output reached 16.12 million tons, 587,000
tons more than in 1995. Other agricultural products, excluding
fruits, all saw increased output.
</P>
<P>
Although floods halted for a time more than 98 percent of the
industrial enterprises' production in the region's major
industrial city Liuzhou, the region's total industrial output grew
by 15.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Some 1.2 million more people shed poverty last year, with their
annual income edging above the 1,100 yuan subsistence line.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi, a region renown for karst landscape and minority
cultures, received half a million overseas tourists, an increase
of 19.5 percent over 1995. 
