<HEADLINE> Official: 3.7 Million Child Laborers in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- There are 3.7 million child
laborers in the Philippines and 60 percent of them are exposed to
hazardous work and activities, a Philippine official said.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government has worked out strategies to tackle
the issue, Lina Laigo, social welfare and development secretary,
was quoted by the Philippine News Agency today as saying.
</P>
<P>
Laigo attributed the increase in child laborers to the lack of
awareness and tolerance, indifference and cultural attitudes aside
 from poverty.
</P>
<P>
She said the authorities have employed a quick action team for
detecting, monitoring and rescuing children in "bonded labor and
hazardous work" in coordination with a national police team.
</P>
<P>
Other measures taken by the government include the setting up
of child watch hotlines to address the child labor issue, said the
secretary.
</P>
<P>
Laigo also called for regional and international cooperation to
hasten the elimination of the most intolerable forms of child
labor in the Philippines and the rest of the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
