<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Traffic Accident in C. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and the
other two seriously wounded in a traffic accident some 55
kilometers east of Uganda's capital Kampala Tuesday, said a
police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Bob Ngobi, the Kampala police chief public relations officer,
said the accident occurred when a lorry collided head-on with a
semitrailer when overtaking another vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The semitrailer then lost its control and knocked a stationary
and finally rammed into a tree in the valley on the side of the
road.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy happened at around 11:30 a.m. Tuesday, witnesses
told local media.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to a hospital in Jinja, some 20
kilometers east of the scene.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the dead were removed away by policemen later
the day. 
