<HEADLINE> Uganda's Coffee Exports to Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 5 (Xinhua)-- Uganda's coffee exports will fall
from 4.2 million bags (60 kilograms per bag) in 1995-96 season to
less than 3.8 million bags in 1996-97, reported the local
newspaper The People today.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Ugandan coffee development authority was
quoted as saying that they cannot meet their quota of the world
market due to drought prevailing across the country during the
period.
</P>
<P>
Uganda exported three million bags of coffee in 1993 and hit a
record high of exporting 4.2 million bags of coffee in 1995-96,
leaving the eastern African country the largest coffee exporter
in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is the biggest foreign exchange earner in Uganda.
