<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Transports Record Passengers in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Macao International Airport
transported 150,772 passengers in February, a record number since
the airport went into operation in November 1995, the Macao
International Airport Company (CAM) said today.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the CAM said the figure was boosted by
holiday traffic and additional chartered flights over the Chinese
Lunar New Year period.
</P>
<P>
In addition, airlines logged extra flights and in many cases
used higher capacity aircraft to meet the demand of increasing
passengers.
</P>
<P>
The airport carried a total of 268,745 passengers between
January and February, compared to 97,050 passengers during the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The total number of passengers who used the airport stood at
1,600,000. That "is well ahead of our expectations and reflects
the growing awareness of the airport and its convenience to
passengers and shippers," said Joao Sousa Moreira, chairman of the
board of directors of the CAM.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, cargo shipment of the airport reached 4,700 tons in
the first two months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The airport will make effective its spring flight schedule from
April 1. The new schedule will add 50 weekly flights to previous
flights. The added flights include those between Macao and
Bangkok, Taiwan, and China's mainland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
