<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Inflation Rate Down in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia posted an inflation rate
of 1.05 percent in February, the lowest in the same periods of the
past five years, Information Minister Harmoko said here today.
</P>
<P>
Following a limited cabinet meeting on economy, Harmoko said
with the 1.05 percent inflation rate in February, inflation rate
in the 1996-97 fiscal year reached 5.29 percent.
</P>
<P>
The February inflation was caused by the increase of prices in
food, garment and housing.
</P>
<P>
On trade situation, Harmoko said, during the period of January
to December 1996, the country's exports reached 49.815 billion
U.S. dollars , while imports stood at 42.869 billion dollars, or a
surplus of 6.946 billion dollars.  
</P>
