public expenditure toward education, job creation and poverty
alleviation, major goals in Namibia's first national development
plan.
</P>
<P>
He said the public sector wage bill, one of the largest
expenditure items in the past, presented the government with a
difficult problem.
</P>
<P>
Namibia reportedly achieved an approximately three percent
growth rate in 1996 due to good rains the country had received
last year after long-period drought. 
