<HEADLINE> Egypt Stresses Importance of Mubarak's Visit to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Egypt's Ambassador to France Ali
Maher today highlighted the importance of President Hosni
Mubarak's talks with his French counterpart Jacques Chirac, who
has been a strong supporter of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Maher told Voice of Arab radio today that the two leaders will
exchange views on the obstacles impeding the peace process and
means of overcoming them.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will meet when Mubarak stops over Paris Friday
en route to his March 10 visit to Washington, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador noted that France backs the Arab stance and
calls for establishing a just and comprehensive peace in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU), especially France, played a major role
in realizing a U.S.-sponsored cease-fire understanding
last April which ended a 17-day Israeli blitz on Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
France has criticized Israel's plan to set up new Jewish
neighborhoods in East Jerusalem and said it is an obstacle
hindering the peace march.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Minister Herve De Charette is currently touring
the Middle East to bolster the peace march.
</P>
<P>
Maher pointed out that there is no contradiction between the
European and U.S. roles in the area as they complement each other.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Israel are reported to have gradually retreated
from excluding Europe from the peace process in the region where
it has been the major financier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
