<HEADLINE> Share Prices Up Marginally on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rose marginally on
the Singapore market in dull trading as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index gained 3.09 points to close at 2,192.53
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 282.52 million units, valued
at 506.2 million Singapore dollars (about 356.48 million US
dollars). Advances overtook declines by 227 to 112, while 265
other counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
OmInd was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 33.54 million units. It was followed by MBF Holdings
which had 12.68 million shares traded. Amsteel warrant was next
with 9.61 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Overseas Union Bank (OUB) Foreign and the Thai Prime Fund
shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of them rose by
40 cents to finish at 11.1 Singapore dollars and 10.4 US dollars
respectively. Cerebos gained 30 cents to 10.4 Singapore dollars,
while the Keppel Corporation was 20 cents higher at 10.4 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 50 cents to close at 16.8 Singapore dollars. Local
soft drink maker F&AMP;N fell by 40 cents to end at 12.5 Singapore
dollars, while Asia Pacific was 30 cents lower at 7.9 Singapore
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
