<HEADLINE> Various Activities to Promote HK's Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Trade Development
Council is to hold various activities here later this month, in a
bid to boost economic exchanges and cooperation between Hong Kong
and the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1986, the council's Beijing office is scheduled
to move into a new location this month. Victor K. Fung, chairman
of the council, will preside over the opening ceremony for the
new office on March 27.
</P>
<P>
The office's services will be expanded, and a library with
economic and trade reference books and computers will be opened.
</P>
<P>
On March 28, the Hong Kong Trade Development Council will hold
a seminar in Beijing focusing on cooperation between Hong
Kong, Beijing, Shanghai and Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of the seminar is to demonstrate to the inland
areas the achievements made by Hong Kong in commerce, trade and
the service industry. Cooperation between Hong Kong and these
areas in finance, banking, transportation also will be discussed
at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a fair to greet Hong Kong's return ot the embrace
of the motherland will be also be held from March 28-31, featuring
exhibits of the economic advantages and characteristics of Hong
Kong, especially its manufacturing and service industries.
</P>
