<HEADLINE> Rapid Growth for Hi-tech Industry in Port City in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The hi-tech industry in Yantai, a
port city in east China's Shandong Province, reported an output
value of 6.4 billion yuan in 1996, up by eight percent over the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The hi-tech industry has become a new economic growth point of
the city, according to officials of the municipal commission of
science and technology.
</P>
<P>
There are now 426 hi-tech enterprises in the city, which have
developed some 500 kinds of hi-tech products. There are three
hi-tech centers in the city, namely the Yantai Hi-tech Industry
Development Zone, the Yantai Science and Technology Park and the
Fushan Hi-tech Industry Park.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government supports technology-intensive projects
with good economic returns, Chen Kaiming, a senior official of the
municipal commission of science and technology said.
</P>
<P>
While stressing major projects, the city has accelerated the
technical renovation of traditional industries and promoted the
use of over 60 sophisticated techniques in the fields of
machine-building, electronics, time pieces, textiles and
petrochemicals.
</P>
<P>
The city expects to report a total income of 30 billion yuan
for the hi-tech industry at the end of the century, or about ten
percent of its total industrial output value, according to the
municipal commission of science and technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
