<HEADLINE> More Farmers in North China Join Old Age Pension Schemes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- In north China's Tangshan,
more farmers are getting access to old age pensions, a benefit
previously enjoyed only by urban residents.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 575,300 farmers in the city's suburbs have
participated in the old age insurance system, with premiums
totaling 102.72 million yuan (12.38 million US dollars), taking
the lead in Hebei province.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, Tangshan, with a population of 1.5
million, has paid more attention to social security in rural
areas, encouraging farmers to buy old-age policies. Many farmers
no longer depend on their children for financial support, but live
on pensions when they are too old to work.
</P>
<P>
Tangshan is about 150 km east of Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
