<HEADLINE> Ethnical, Religious Figures Urged to Safeguard Unity, Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A leader from China's religious
circle today called on ethnical and religious figures to assist
the central authorities in safeguarding stability and unity, and
in firmly combating separatist activities.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Puchu, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference and chairman of
its Subcommittee of Nationalities and Religion, made the remark on
a meeting of the subcommittee today.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, also president of the Chinese Buddhist Association, said,
"the freedom of religious belief for all ethnical groups should
specially be respected and protected when we are fighting against
separatist activities."
</P>
<P>
When reviewing important expositions set forth by Deng
Xiaoping, the late senior Chinese leader, on the national
minorities and religious affairs, he said, there would be no
all-round restoration and implementation of the Party's policies
on nationalities and religions without Deng's ideological line on
the emancipation of the people's mind and seeking truth from
facts.
</P>
<P>
The work concerning nationalities and religions is of great
importance, which concerns the reunification of the motherland and
prosperity and development in ethnic minority regions, and is
closely related to the overall situation across the country.
</P>
<P>
He urged that CPPCC National Committee members to perform their
duties well and reflect popular feelings of the ethnical and
religious affairs promptly.
</P>
<P>
Although religion is not the basic feature of an ethnic group,
Zhao noted, the two issues are interelated and inseparable, and
improper handling of the religious issue will be detrimental to
ethnical unity and social stability, and consequently hamper
economic and cultural progress in national minority regions.
</P>
<P>
The Subcommittee of Nationalities and Religions, which
comprises more than 150 members, represents various ethnic and
religious groups.
</P>
<P>
In today's meeting, the subcommittee also defined its work this
year, which will focus on promotion of economic, socialist ethical
and cultural progress in ethnic minority areas based on unity,
stability and development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
