<HEADLINE> Eastern Airlines, American Airlines Sign Codesharing MOU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Though routes to China are not
yet opened, American Airlines (AA), the largest in the US, will be
able to extend its service to Chinese cities by allowing China's
Eastern Airlines to use its "AA" designator code.
</P>
<P>
This will be possible after a memorandum of understanding of
cooperation signed recently between the two airlines in Dallas is
approved by the Chinese and US governments.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the agreement, the two airlines will use Los
Angeles and San Francisco as the transit points to extend their
routes by exchanging codes.
</P>
<P>
For example, Eastern Airlines will sell the flights operated by
AA between Los Angeles or San Francisco to New York, Chicago,
Washington and Dallas as its own, by putting its "MU" code on AA
flights.
</P>
<P>
And in turn, AA's routes will be extended to Shanghai and
Beijing when flights of the Eastern Airlines from Los Angeles and
San Francisco use AA's designation.
</P>
<P>
"The cooperation, which is a common practice internationally,
will enable the two air companies to increase routes at lower
costs and reduce the transit flight rates of the passengers,"
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
