<HEADLINE> Fujian Attracts More Investment from Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Fujian, a coastal province which
faces Taiwan across a strait, had approved 4,533 Taiwan-funded
enterprises by the end of last year, involving more than nine
billion US dollars, said a local government advisor here today.
</P>
<P>
In a press conference organized by the Fifth Session of the
Eighth Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
National Committee which has been in session since the end of
February, You Dexin, chairman of the CPPCC Fujian Provincial
Committee expressed his confidence in seeing more Taiwan funds
pouring into Fujian in the near future.
</P>
<P>
You expressed the hope that transportation and business circles
in Taiwan would forge closer ties with related departments in
Fujian to promote direct shipping services between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question from a Voice of America reporter
about members of Taiwan mafia seeking a safe haven in Fujian, You
said this is "possible" given recent crackdowns on mafia
activities in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"These elements will harm public security in Fujian," he said.
"Police departments in Fujian have been cooperating closely with
local residents in ferreting out any criminals that may have
hidden in Fujian."
</P>
<P>
He called for police in Fujian and Taiwan to exchange related
information and cooperate with each other in cracking down on
crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
