<HEADLINE> China Witnesses Rapid Development In National Defense Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China has made remarkable progress
in developing a number of important weapons last year, according
to reports from the National Work Conference of the National
Defense Technological Industry.
</P>
<P>
The country has made breakthroughs in some major technology
projects and set up a group of modern and well-equipped key
laboratories, it was announced at the conference.
</P>
<P>
Test launches of some types of missiles and satellites have
been successful.
</P>
<P>
Also in 1996, 89 research achievements won state-level awards.
</P>
<P>
The industry has been taking vigorous measures to create
products for civil use by giving full play to its high-tech
capabilities.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the output value of such products has been
growing at an annual rate of 20 percent, which has contributed 80
percent to the industry's total output value last year. The goods
have been exported to over 30 countries.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more than 2,500 technological advances created for
the military have entered the domestic and global markets,
contributing greatly to the development of the economy and
increasing the country's annual output value by several billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The industry will implement its long-term development strategy
of shifting its high technology for national defense into civil
use.
</P>
<P>
Before the end of this century, it will redouble its efforts to
develop civil airplanes, satellites, nuclear power plants and
telecommunications systems.  
</P>
