<HEADLINE> Top Advisory Body Receives over 2,000 Proposals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China's top advisory body, which
is in its annual session, has received 2,498 proposals since its
last session held a year ago, and 95.3 percent of these proposals
have been examined and filed.
</P>
<P>
The proposals to the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) came from its members,
non-communist parties and the relevant organization, and 77
percent of the members of the CPPCC National Committee have
submitted proposals, said Zhang Wenshou, vice-chairman of the
Subcommittee for Handling Proposals today in a report to the
second Plenary Meeting of the Fifth Session of the Eighth CPPCC
National Committee.
</P>
<P>
He further noted that 2,334 proposals, or 98.1 percent, were
handled by February 14 of this year; and 1,937 proposals, or 83
percent, were settled or ready to be settled.
</P>
<P>
The proposals involves a wide-range of aspects, including
economic development, science and technology, education, culture,
public health, sports, politics and laws, the united front work,
personnel and welfare, nationalities and religions, and the most
proposals concern economic affairs, 1,077 in number, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the proposals have been forwarded to 161
units, including the institutions of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China, and the relevant ministries or
commissions and departments directly under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Zhang said, the proposals have drawn attention of the
departments concerned, and most of these departments have
organized groups of competent people, and set up or improve their
networks to handle them.  
</P>
