<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A senior member of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) called for
enhanced efforts nationwide to provide more job opportunities for
laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
Jin Shuping, a member of the Standing Committee of the Eighth
CPPCC National Committee, made the call at a general session of
the committee here today.
</P>
<P>
Jin proposed the following to create more jobs:
</P>
<P>
First, efforts should be made to strengthen a comprehensive
development of agriculture so that as much rural surplus labor can
be absorbed locally as possible.
</P>
<P>
Second, in industrial restructuring, state enterprises should
try their best to find a way out for their own surplus labor.
</P>
<P>
Third, development of service industries should be speeded
up.
</P>
<P>
Fourth, non-public economic sectors should play a greater
role in executing reemployment programs. And
</P>
<P>
Fifth, the government can organize labor export in a planned
way.
</P>
<P>
Jin, who is also chairman of the All-China Federation of
Industry and Commerce, called on federation of industry and
commerce organizations at all levels to take an active part in
employment programs launched by the government to make their "due
contributions to reform, opening-up, economic development and
social stability." 
