<HEADLINE> Exhibitions Bring Prosperity to in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, MARCH 5 (Xinhua) -- Exhibitions and trade fairs have
become a major contributor to the economic growth of the coastal
city of Dalian in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Such events to be held in the port city this year will generate
a turnover of 20 billion yuan and are growing into a pillar
industry, said Vice-Mayor Li Yongjin.
</P>
<P>
Among the dozens of shows and fairs held last year was s the
Dalian International Garment Fair, which attracted 400,000
visitors from home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
To cater to the increasing need for displays and fairs, the
city built the Xinghai Exhibition Center, which covers a total
floor space of 95,000 square meters,
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two exhibitions were held in the center from the
beginning of July to the end of 1996, involving 6,000 Chinese and
overseas companies. The total turnover reached 12 billion yuan,
including 700 million US dollars of foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Exhibitions boost Dalian's service sector, as local hotels and
restaurants are full, telecommunications departments and post
offices are kept busy, and most taxi drivers work
round-the-clock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
