<HEADLINE> Spark Program Advances Economy in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 5 (Xinhua) -- In 1991, the per capita income
was only 210 yuan in Wencheng, a small mountainous town in east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the town reported the per capita income was 6.3
times the 1991 figure, and a total output value of more than 86
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed the changes to the launch of a Spark
Program a decade ago across the province. The program disseminates
applied techniques to help jump start the rural economy.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade or so, more than 4,000 projects related to
the program have been implemented in the province, having produced
more than 50 billion yuan of newly added value and over ten
billion yuan in profits and taxes.
</P>
<P>
Some 1.28 million farmers received technical training in the
past five years, the majority of whom having grasped some applied
techniques, play a leading role in local economic development.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
