<HEADLINE> Fujian's Ports Prepared for Direct Shipping with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Preparations have been made by the
ports of Fuzhou and Xiamen, in east China's Fujian Province, to
begin direct navigation with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The two ports are the first test sites designated by the
ministries of Communications and Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation for direct shipping to nearby Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Construction of basic facilities at the ports has been
accelerated, and the ports now have more than 140 sea transport
berths, including dozens of berths that can accommodate 10,000
tons or more, according to Yang Shuilai, director of the
provincial port office.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that the berths can be used to load and unload
containers, bulk cargo and oil tanks, and are also capable of
transporting large numbers of passengers.  
</P>
