<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Hangzhou Expressway to Open to Traffic in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- An expressway running from
Shanghai, China's largest city, to Hangzhou, capital of eastern
China's Zhejiang Province, is scheduled to open to traffic in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Once completed, the 151-km expressway, part of the
country's National Route 320, will link the Shanghai-Nanjing
Expressway in the north and the Hangzhou-Ningbo Expressway in the
south.
</P>
<P>
The expressway is expected to give a boost to the Yangtze River
delta's economy by improving the region's transportation network.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai section of the expressway, stretching more than 48
kilometers, will cost a total of nearly 2.1 billion yuan,
including 60 million US dollars in World Bank loans.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time Shanghai has used overseas funds for road
construction. 
</P>
