<HEADLINE> NZ to Try Hidden Speed Cameras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand police will begin
using hidden speed cameras on roads from July this year in central
North Island.
</P>
<P>
If proved successful, the camera will be introduced throughout
the country after a 12-month trial. Roads in central North Island
are considered to carry high risks of accidents.
</P>
<P>
