<HEADLINE> Top Seed Crashes Out in Scottsdale Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Byron Black of Zimbabwe upset
top-seeded Marcelo Rios of Chile 6-1, 4-6, 7-6 (7-5) in the
Scottsdale Tennis tournament in Scottsdasle on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Rios was not the only seed eliminated in the tournament.
Spain's Javier Sanchez also ousted No. 5 Andre Agassi of the
United States 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
After Australian Patrick Rafter beat No. 6 Alberto Berasategui
of Spain 6-3, 6-1 in the last match Tuesday night, the tournament
was left with three seeded players who got past the first round.
</P>
<P>
Rios, the world's sixth-ranked player, failed to advance for
the first time in five 1997 tournaments. The Chilean reached the
1996 Scottsdale final before losing to Wayne Ferreira, this year's
No. 2 seed, who lost Monday.
</P>
<P>
No. 4 Albert Costa and No. 8 Richey Reneberg advanced.
</P>
<P>
Costa, one of six Spanish players involved in the 32-player
field, beat Marc-Kevin Goellner of Germany 6-4, 7-6 (7-2), and
Reneberg followed on Stadium Court with a 7-6 (7-1), 0-6, 6-1
victory over Vincent Spadea. 
</P>
