<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading South African newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
The Citizen
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa's economy could grow by close to three percent
in 1997, after 3.1 percent in 1996 and 3.4 percent in 1995,
Reserve Bank Governor Chris Stals said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Star
</P>
<P>
-- Rand Water, the leading water supplier in the Greater
Johannesburg Metropolitan, announced on Tuesday it would increase
the price of bulk water supply to town councils in Gauteng
Province.
</P>
<P>
Business Day
</P>
<P>
-- President Nelson Mandela, currently on a Southeast Asian
tour, on Tuesday called for closer links between the seven-member
Association of Southeast Asian Nations and the 12-member Southern
African Development Community, which he holds the chairmanship.
</P>
<P>
Sowetan
</P>
<P>
-- Police are investigating arson after the blaze that
destroyed more than half of the Munitoria, the Pretoria City
Council headquarters, a source said on Tuesday. 
</P>
