<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Raises Product Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Municipality, the
largest manufacturing center in China, is raising product
standards with stronger administration of quality certificates.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the municipality took the lead in the country by
setting up Shanghai Accreditation Center to issue qualification
certificates to firms with good product quality.
</P>
<P>
So far, 108 foreign-funded, state-owned and township
enterprises in the city have obtained certificates for quality.
</P>
<P>
Accreditation can give enterprises incentive to achieve
greater economic efficiency. A survey showed that after the firms
received accreditation 88.8 percent of firms enjoyed increased
sales volume and 70.4 percent saw more profit.
</P>
<P>
This year, the local government will check the quality of 500
products manufactured by the machine, electronics and auto industries.
</P>
<P>
The accreditation center will also continue to encourage firms
to apply for certificates. This year 300 firms are expected to
pass accreditation standards.
</P>
<P>
China now has more than 20 accreditation organizations of
various kinds, which combined have issued more than 1,000 quality
certificates to firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
