<HEADLINE> Russian FM Sees OSCE Security Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov wants the Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE) to play a more important role in the European
security system.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks today while meeting the visiting
Secretary-general of the OSCE, Giancarlo Aragona, who arrived here
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Primakov said the OSCE, as the organization with the greatest
influence and with the most functions among European
organizations, could be the basis of the European security
framework.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Primakov also expressed his wish that the
OSCE speed up the formulation of European Security Charter. He
said the charter would play an important role in the course of
building a European security system.
</P>
<P>
The OSCE, formerly the Conference on Security and Cooperation
in Europe (CSCE), focuses on discussing security, economic
cooperation and cultural exchanges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
