<HEADLINE> Ukraine, U.S. to Promote Strategic Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Foreign Minister Gennady
Udovenkn says he is satisfied with the strategic partnership his
country and the United States have achieved over recent years.
</P>
<P>
Udovenkn made the statement today ahead of a trip to Ottawa and
Washington. He said the Ukraine and the U.S. had pledged to
promote this relationship to the largest degree.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Washington on Friday, the Ukrainian
minister will meet U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to discuss wide-range issues of bilateral
relations in the framework of the Ukrainian-U.S. strategic
partnership.
</P>
<P>
The two officials will also try to reach an agreement on the
Ma-Gore Commission, which was set up in September 1996 to
strengthen bilateral cooperation in the economy, politics,
military and security, according to the local press.
</P>
<P>
Udovenkn said the commission was of great significance to
business circles of Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interfax News Agency, Udovenkn will also talk
with the U.S. Congress and business circles.
</P>
<P>
His discussions with Congress will include disarmament,
supervision of arms sales and the political situation in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Udovenkn will visit Canada for two days starting from
Wednesday. Then he will fly to Washington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
