<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doctor Warns Thais Against Hepatitis Risk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Thai people are warned against
hepatitis risk as many of them carry the hepatitis virus, a local
newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
About six to 10 percent of all the Thai people are carriers of
the type-b hepatitis virus, "The Nation" quoted a senior
government doctor as saying.
</P>
<P>
The type-b hepatitis virus may be transmitted through blood
transfusions, pregnancy or contacts, said Dr. Taweesak Tanwandee
of Siriraj hospital.
</P>
<P>
Taweesak suggested that frequent alcohol drinkers or those who
have a history of type-b or type-c hepatitis undergo medical
checkups regularly.  
</P>
</TEXT>
