<HEADLINE> Immunization Drive to Be launched in Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Delhi state government is
launching a special immunization program from March 10 to March 16
to cover children upto five years age against vaccine preventable
disease, The Hindustan Time said today.
</P>
<P>
State Health and Education Minister Harsh Vardhan said on
Monday that during the week-long period, these children would be
screened for their immunization status regarding a number of
vaccines such as polio and measles vaccines.
</P>
<P>
He said that between 75,000 and 100,000 children are expected
to be immunized during the special drive.  
</P>
