<HEADLINE> Two Seeds Out in World Indoor Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Fourth seed Jan Siemerink and
six-seeded Paul Haarhuis, both from the Netherlands, were
eliminated from the 750,000-U.S.-Dollar World Indoor Tennis
tournament in Rotterdam on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Siemerink struggled to two tiebreakers, but failed to avoid his
failure. He conceded the match to Daniel Vacek of Czech Republic
6-7 (3-7), 6-7 (2-7).
</P>
<P>
It was also a bad day for Siemerink's fellow countryman
Haarhuis. Haarhuis could not resist the strong shots from his
first-round rival Martin Sinner and lost to the German 3-6, 4-6.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Richard Krajicek changed the Dutch lackluster
performances of the day and ousted Czech Martin Damm 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Enqvist of Sweden, the third seed, also went through by
outplaying another Czech player Bohdan Ulihrach 7-5, 6-7 (4-7),
6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
