<HEADLINE> South China's Island Province To Boost Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China's Hainan Island, a well-known
scenic tropical spot, has set a goal of attracting 4.8 million
tourists this year.
</P>
<P>
This will include 350,000 overseas visitors, who are expected
to bring in 95 million US dollars worth of foreign exchange for
the island province.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Hainan also expects to earn nearly 6.5 billion
yuan from domestic visitors this year. During Spring Festival,
which fell on February 7, the number of visitors in coastal Sanya,
the second largest city after the capital of Haikou, was reported
at 159,000, up nearly 34 percent from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to develop a series of measures to boost
local tourism, such as cultural and other festivals, to help the
island increase its returns from the industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
