<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures for 1996: Science (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China in 1996 spent 10.985 billion
yuan in science and technology, 2.1 percent more than the budgeted
figure.
</P>
<P>
As a result, more than 2,000 major scientific and technological
results were achieved, and industries supported by high and new
technologies developed rapidly.
</P>
<P>
These results included the triple recovery technology using
polymer resins, which was introduced in the petroleum industry,
the 622-megabyte synchronous digital hierarchy optical fibre
transmission system applied on the 700-km line between Chengdu and
Panzhihua, and the "Shuguang"-series of high-performance
computers, which played a key role in promoting the use of
information technology in national economic development.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that by the end of last year, China had 165
national science associations and societies, covering almost all
academic fields. Between 1978 and the end of 1996, these
organizations had sponsored more than 40,000 academic activities
attracting six million participants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
