<HEADLINE> Beijing University Awards Mrs. Sackler </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The title of honorary director of
the Arthur M. Sackler Museum of Art and Archaeology was bestowed
upon Mrs. Jill Sackler at a recent ceremony at Beijing
University.
</P>
<P>
Opened in 1992, the Sackler Museum of Art and Archaeology was
co-established by Beijing University and the AMS Foundation for
the Arts, Science and Humanities. The museum has collected over
ten thousand cultural artifacts.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Jill Sackler is the president and chief executive officer
of the AMS Foundation, which funded the establishment of Arthur
M. Sackler Museum of Art and Archaeology and the Jill Sackler
sculpture garden at the university. Mrs. Sackler also financed the
"Jill Sackler Cup Calligraphy Competition" which has since taken
place three times.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Liang, deputy president of Beijing University, Zheng
Guangrong, deputy director of the museum section of the National
Bureau of Relics, and Qian Xinzhong, former minister of Public
Health were among those who attended the ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
