<DOCNO> XIE19970305.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Unveils New Plan to Wipe Out Child Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso today announced a new program to bring children
back to school and wipe out child labor in the country.
</P>
<P>
The program, known as "Brazil, Child Citizen," will be kicked
off next month to benefit initially 30,000 children and eventually
50,000, Cardoso told "the President Speaks Out" TV program.
</P>
<P>
"I am asking governors, prefects and businessmen, in
particular, to elevate their vigilance against child and teenage
labor," the president said of the government initiative.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to join forces as well as human and financial
resources to eradicate child labor from the countryside forever
because a child's place is in school," he added.
</P>
<P>
Currently, about 3.8 million Brazilian children under the age
of 14 go to workplace instead of school. They account for 25
percent of the rural labor force in this South American country.
</P>
<P>
The new program is part of a national campaign launched by
President Cardoso on September 6, 1996, when he signed three
documents on the eradication of child labor in Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
