<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Calls for Efforts to Ease Albanian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria has called on the
international community to take effective and urgent measures to
help solve the Albanian crisis and prevent it from expanding to a
broader area.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by Bulgarian Foreign Ministry on Tuesday
night, said the most important thing for easing the dangerous
situation was to supply urgent humanitarian aid to Albania, with
help from international financial associations while the
diplomatic efforts were underway.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Bulgaria regarded peaceful and democratic
means as the only solution to the current crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian crisis grew out of public rage over the collapse
of popular, pyramid-type investments in which nearly every
Albanian family lost money.
</P>
<P>
The worsening situation in this country has forced the
government to order curfews, roadblocks and declare a state of
emergency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
