<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Public Health (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The average life expectancy of
China's 1.2 billion people has doubled from 1949's figure of 35
years, a 1996 report of the Ministry of Public Health said.
</P>
<P>
The incidence of infectious diseases has dropped to 116 people
per 100,000 people in 1996 from 20,000 people per 100,000 in the
early 1950s.
</P>
<P>
Leprosy has been eradicated or controlled in more than 90
percent of counties, and the number of patients declined to 11,000
from some 500,000 in the early 1950s.
</P>
<P>
The incidence rate of tuberculosis has fallen to 523 people per
100,000 people, compared with 3,000 to 4,000 people per 100,000
more than 40 years ago. The cure rate of the disease stands at 90
percent.
</P>
<P>
China has set up 137 disease prevention agencies, staffed with
nearly 30,000 personnel.
</P>
<P>
The mortality rate of pregnant women and new mothers has
dropped to 62 people per 100,000 people, down from 1,500 per
100,000 in 1949. The death rate of infants lowered to 36 per
thousand from 250 per thousand in the same period.
</P>
<P>
At present, 85 percent of children in China's urban and rural
areas are immunized against infectious diseases.
</P>
<P>
China has had 5,895 epidemic prevention stations -- 25 times
the figure in the 1950s -- employing more than 270,000 people.
Meanwhile, about 134,000 people work at 3,179 health care agencies
across the country.
</P>
<P>
In other progress, on May 15, 1996, the Chinese capital Beijing
officially forbade smoking in public places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970305.0267 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC Seeks to Strengthen Ties With Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Southern African
Development Community (SADC) wants to strengthen trade and
technological exchanges with the Southern American Common Market
(Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
Kaire Mbuende, the executive secretary of the SADC, made the
remarks when meeting with Brazilian Foreign Minister Luiz Felipe
Lampreia in Brasilia on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"This trip is the first step towards bringing together the two
regions, which still use Europe as a bridge for their trade," said
Kaire Mbuende.
</P>
<P>
"Like us, the Mercosur is struggling with the questions of
integration and development, and so we feel that an exchange of
experiences is very important."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the two trade blocs had a mutual interest in
pressing for a reduction on agriculture tariffs worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The SADC, which was established in 1994, groups Angola,
Botswana, Zimbabwe, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia,
Swaziland, Tanzania, Zambia and South Africa. Its population
amounts to 140 million, with a gross domestic product of about 150
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, which was established in 1994, is made up of
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
