<HEADLINE> Monaco Upset Newcastle in UEFA Quarter-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- French league leaders Monaco moved
one step closer to the UEFA title as they edged England's last
survivors Newcastle United 1-0 on Tuesdasy in their away-match at
St James' Park in the quarter-final first-leg match.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian striker Sonny Anderson scored his fourth goal in the
tournament after 19-year-old Thierry Henry outpaced opponents'
defence and cut the ball back. Anderson scored the only goal of
the match in the 60th minute.
</P>
<P>
The French league leaders had won all three of their previous
away legs against Cracow, Hamburg and Borussia Moenchengladbach.
</P>
<P>
It was only the second home defeat in European comeptitions
for the Newcastle team.
</P>
<P>
Without three star strikers Alan Shearer, Les Ferdinand and
Faustino Asprilla, as well as injury-plagued veteran Peter
Beardsley, Newcastle seemed far from powerful as they used to be.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches of the day, favourites Inter Milan of
Italy earned a 1-1 draw in the away match to Anderlecht of
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Maurizio Ganz scored a late equaliser after Bruno Versavel had
given Anderlecht a first-half lead with a neat half-volley.
</P>
<P>
Tenerife of Spain, which had gone into the match riding high
on last week's 4-0 league win over powerhouse Barcelona, failed
to revive their momentum and lost to the Danish opponent Brondy
0-1.
</P>
<P>
It was a sad day for the Spanish fans. Valencia also was
whitewashed by Germany's Schalke 04 0-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
