<HEADLINE> China Encourages More Steel Ventures to List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Steel companies seeking to raise
funds by issuing stocks publicly has government support, said Wang
Wanbin, vice minister of Metallurgical Industry.
</P>
<P>
A number of steel ventures were already on the waiting list to
place stocks in the near future, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
"It will prove to be a wise choice in the end to hold shares in
steel companies," said Wang, adding that the current malaise of
the steel-making industry, common in a market economy, wouldn't
last.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese steel-making industry has bright prospects given
its advantages in equipment and management personnel," he said.
</P>
<P>
The successful overseas placement of stocks by the Ma'anshan
Steel Company in 1993 has demonstrated worldwide confidence in
China's steel industry, said the senior official.
</P>
<P>
Wang said he believes the to-be-listed steel ventures will
follow the steps of Ma'anshan Steel Company and achieve even
greater success. 
