<HEADLINE> Macedonia Uneasy Over Situation in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian Foreign Minister
Ljubomir Frckovski said on Monday that Macedonia felt uneasy over
the situation in Albania.
</P>
<P>
"Macedonia has a feeling of unease over the situation in
Albania and hopes that the Albanian authorities will find a
peaceful solution on the premise of conforming to the principle of
democracy," Frckovski told the press.
</P>
<P>
He said the situation along the two countries' borders was
normal.
</P>
<P>
Albanian people have been protesting out of rage since January,
and blame the government for losing their life savings in
collapsed schemes.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government ordered a state of emergency on Sunday
in an attempt to subdue the protests and violence. Under the
order, people will not be permitted to walk in groups of more than
four, newspapers must submit their material to the Defense Council
before publication, and police may shoot at anyone who throws
objects at them. 
</P>
