Province has been making efforts to develop the chain-store
business in the past few years, and had 43 companies with 735
chain stores by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Priority has been given to developing meat and vegetable stores
to provide greater convenience for people in their daily life,
local officials say.
</P>
<P>
The province has been supporting the chain-store sector with
funding and policies, and taxes for the business have been reduced.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial plan, the number of chain-store
companies will reach 100 by the end of the century, and the number
of chain stores, 3,000, contributing about five percent of the
province's total retail sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
