<HEADLINE> Tornado Kills One, Displaces Many in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- One was killed and many left
homeless today as a tornado swept across a mountainous region in
southwestern Bulgaria, the state-run BTA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The strong wind also uprooted big trees and caused huge
property damage on its way plowing through the region of Pirin,
which is 1,200 meters above the sea level, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The worst hit was a village called Oshava, where the death toll
was reported. There, all roofs of the houses sheltering the 160
families were ripped off, and dozens of residences destroyed.
</P>
<P>
As most residents of the village are retired workers over 50,
they could not afford to rebuild their houses and some reportedly
had to take shelter in crowded basements. 
</P>
