<HEADLINE> Poland to Participate in Talks on NATO: Danish Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Danish Prime Minister Poul
Rasmussen, on a visit to Poland, said here today that Poland will
be invited to participate in a forthcoming conference on NATO's
enlargement.
</P>
<P>
Poland would be among the first non-NATO states to participate
in negotiations on joining the organization at its Madrid
conference to be held this July, said Rasmussen.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister arrived in Poland on Monday for a three-day
official visit.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with his Polish counterpart, Wlodzimierz
Cimoszewicz, on Monday, Rasmussen expressed Denmark's support for
Poland's bid to join NATO and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers were satisfied with bilateral
relations, and with their trade volume of 1.5 billion U.S. dollars
last year. They signed an agreement under which Denmark will
grant financial aid as well as technical assistance to Poland.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Rasmussen also met Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski, Speaker of the Sejm (House of Representatives) Jozef
Zych, and Speaker of the Senate Adam Struzik. 
