<HEADLINE> Thai Patient Caught for Selling Drug in Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A man was arrested Tuesday in a
hospital in central Thailand on the suspicion of directing
amphetamines trade from his hospital bed.
</P>
<P>
Police found 24,000 amphetamine tablets, bank account books, a
mobile phone, and a loaded pistol after they raided the ward in
Bencharom Hospital in Lop Buri province where the suspect stayed,
The Nation reported.
</P>
<P>
The 41-year-old man was admitted into the hospital last month
after an accident and nurses found that he had many visitors every
day and the door of his ward was always locked during their
meetings, the local newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Police seized the man on a tip-off. 
