<HEADLINE> Water Filter Sale Rises in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The sales of water filter rose 20
percent in the first two months this year as Macao residents are
fearing of worsening water pollution, the Macao Daily News reports
today.
</P>
<P>
Water filters and machines making distilled water have become
increasingly popular here over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Schools, private institutions and families are the leading
buyers of the gadgets.
</P>
<P>
The report says that local people worry more and more about
their living environment, where sewage water increased rapidly,
and may contaminate drinking water. Some people say that ever tap
water may be polluted by rusty pipes.
</P>
<P>
Most buyers of family-use filters favor the high quality ones,
which sell at more than 5,000 patacas (about 633 U.S. dollars)
each. They also tend to buy the machine in summer season.
</P>
</TEXT>
