<HEADLINE> China, Britain Agree on HK Handover Ceremony Coverage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The application for media
coverage of Hong Kong's handover ceremony will begin from March
15 through April 7, according to a notice issued by the
Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG) here today.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing after the JLG ended a meeting on the
arrangements for the coverage of Hong Kong's handover ceremony,
Zhao Jihua, senior Chinese representative on the JLG, said that
Hong Kong's handover ceremony is a major event jointly held by the
Chinese and British governments.
</P>
<P>
He said that after a friendly and practical discussion held
this morning, the Chinese and British sides on the JLG reached
consensus on the notice about the arrangements for the coverage of
Hong Kong's handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The handover ceremony is to be held in Hong Kong at midnight on
June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Hugh Davies, senior British representative on the JLG, said
that the two sides on the JLG welcome journalists representing
media organizations from all over the world to cover the handover
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
He said, "I very much look forward to as many as possible
international and local press being interested in participating,
recording and reporting on the handover ceremony."
</P>
<P>
Replying a reporter's question, he said that some 6,000 media
representatives are expected to come.
</P>
<P>
According to the notice, the JLG has entrusted the Hong Kong
government to handle the news media application to cover the
event.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong government has set up a handover ceremony
coordination office to accept news media's application for the
handover ceremony coverage.
</P>
<P>
The office will confirm the qualifications of the journalists
who apply for the coverage according to the normal internationally
accepted practice.
</P>
<P>
The office will distribute application forms for the coverage
on March 15 and the deadline for the application is set on April
7.
</P>
<P>
A press center and a broadcasting center will be set up to
facilitate media coverage of the handover ceremony. 
</P>
