low level although Bangladesh enjoys a favorable trade surplus by
exporting jute goods and some traditional items.
</P>
<P>
Ramos, coming to Bangladesh on the second leg of his
three-nation trip to the subcontinent, flew here from New Delhi.
He leaves Dhaka for Islamabad Friday.
</P>
<P>
A big delegation, comprising Foreign Minister Domingo Siazon,
three other ministers and some top traders and industrialists from
the Philippines, is accompanying President Ramos.
</P>
<P>
