<HEADLINE> Thai Official Calls for Low-cost Medical Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand should pay more attention
to the development of medical technology to overcome local health
problems, especially that with the cost affordable to the public,
a senior Thai health official said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of an international medical
exhibition, Vitura Saengsingkaew, permanent secretary of the Thai
Public Health Ministry, called for application and development of
medical technology which would not make patients heavily depend on
them.
</P>
<P>
Medical technology should be directed at problems with low
cost, safety and less side-effects, he was quoted as saying by
local newspapers.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that the patients have the rights to know
information about both benefits and side-effects of medical
methods.
</P>
<P>
He noted that expensive and highly-sophisticated medical
technology and equipment, such as computerized tomography
scanners, should be made accessible to all.
</P>
<P>
Currently, medical costs are generally high in Thailand as some
hospitals pay more attention to profits instead of the effects of
medical technology used.  
</P>
</TEXT>
