<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today inspected his home state Arkansas which was the worst hit
area by tornadoes and thunderstorms last weekend.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 people had been killed, hundreds of others injured
and hundreds of houses destroyed in five states including
Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
Shaking his head in dismay over the devastation that surrounded
him, Clinton said, "I've been down every one of these streets
before. I've been in every one of these stores." He comforted the
victims by saying, "I wish there were more I could say and do."
</P>
