<HEADLINE> European Shares Up, London, Frankfurt Hit New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe all
staged a strong rally and ended sharply higher today, with London
and Frankfurt closing at new record highs.
</P>
<P>
Optimism over interest rates and strong gilts and futures
helped British shares to a record closing high, with the FTSE 100
index up 50.6 points at 4,357.7
</P>
<P>
Hopes that interest rates will remain unchanged before
Britain's general election boosted bonds and enabled the FTSE 100
index to shrug off an unspectacular start on Wall Street, traders
said.
</P>
<P>
German shares in Frankfurt also closed today's session at a new
record high, buoyed by the strength of bonds and the dollar and
overnight Dow gains, with the DAX-30 index 56.8 points up at
3,320.66.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse finished a bullish day only slightly lower
than its record high reached on February 18, with the CAC-40 index
gaining 51.43 points at 2,651.69, pushed upwards by Wall Streent's
gains Monday, firmer bonds and a strong dollar.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index closed up 50.6 points at 4,357.7. In
Frankfurt, the DAX-30 index ended 56.8 points higher at 3,320.66.
The Paris CAC-40 index finished 51.43 points up at 2,651.69.
