<HEADLINE> Dow Plunges While Tech Shares Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Leading technology shares
continued to rebound on Wall Street today, but stocks turned
mostly lower late in the session as interest rates rose again in
the bond market.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 66.20 points, or nearly 1
percent, to 6,858.72.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with the volume reaching 536.22
million shares, up from 432.68 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 4.36 to 790.95, and
the NYSE composite index fell 1.66 to 415.68.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 6.20 to 1,317.38, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 2.22 to 597.04.
</P>
<P>
Bonds gave up some early gains after the Commerce Department
reported that January's warm weather in the Northeast and South
helped push sales of new homes to a nearly 11-year high. The 8.6
percent increase from December's tally was stronger than predicted
by economists.
</P>
<P>
And in another report, a private research group said its index
of future economic activity rose 0.3 percent in January, beating
expectations of about 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
As bond prices rose and declined for the day, the yield on the
30-year Treasury rose from late Monday's 6.83 percent to 6.68
percent, the highest finish since late January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
